Important information for those Interested:
  the 81 "Books" are dirictions for only 81 MODELS. It is NOT a collection of every Origami book released in the last decade.
  Beyond that information, I can inform all that the models range from super easy to decently challanging, (I'm a folding addict, and have not yet found a model I couldn't make.)
  So from my viewpoint: Some good fun here, but two thirds too dull to even look at.

81 Origami models, not 81 books.
But the models are well documented, hence making it easy for novices and intermediate users.
